the meeting is mainly intended to hear the un arms inspection chief &apos;s report on whether iraq has complied with the un security council resolution 1441 passed on november 8 last year , which orders iraq to disarm .
white house spokesman fleischer said blix hasn &apos;t provided any reason for people to believe that iraq is complying with the security council resolution 1441 .
he told reporters : &quot; today the world hasn &apos;t got any relief from the news coming from new york , convinced that hussein has shown arms inspectors that he is disarming .
the situation is exactly the opposite . &quot;
asked when the united states will propose a follow-up resolution aimed to implement the security council resolution 1441 , fleischer indicated &quot; it &apos;s too early to tell , &quot; but the united states will discuss with its allies on its content and terms .
countries such as france , russia and china still propose tougher arms inspection for iraq instead of a us-led war against iraq .
