however , he insisted on the timetable bush has set , saying that the united nations has got only &quot; a few weeks not months &quot; to test peaceful disarmament with iraq , which will then be followed by military actions .
new york times : white house studies sanctions against north korea
( afp , washington ) citing us officials , the new york times today reported that white house is studying sanctions against north korea once pyongyang fails to abandon its development of nuclear weapons .
the report pointed out that these sanctions will include interdicting north korea &apos;s arms shipment and cutting off the channels through which north koreans in japan send money to north korea .
the report pointed out that the pentagon and the state department are working on the detailed plans for sanctions so that the united states can respond promptly any time when north korea takes its new steps to pursue the development of nuclear weapons .
according to the new york times report , the first step will be to urge the un security council , perhaps in the next two weeks , to denounce north korea &apos;s recent measures to develop nuclear weapons such as withdrawing from the nuclear non-proliferation treaty and reactivating its frozen nuclear facility at yongbyon that is capable of producing weapons-grade plutonium .
yet , the pacific allies of washington authorities are still opposed to the idea of sanctioning against north korea , while the un security council may still focus on the issue of iraq for the next few weeks .
in the meantime , the new york times report pointed out , many us officials are concerned if the united states launches attacks against iraq , north korea may use the opportunity to promote its weapons production .
us troops to conduct training on philippine hostage island
( afp , manila , philippines , february 17 ) the us military trainers will be sent to the hostage island of jolo in the philippines this year to assist the country in coping with the terrorist threat from the rebel islamic groups .
bunye , a spokesperson for philippine president arroyo , said : &quot; this military exercise will be part of overall and ongoing defense and security cooperation activities between the philippines and the united states , and will continue to focus on enhancing our ability to combat terrorist threats and defend ourselves . &quot;
he pointed out in a statement : &quot; the detailed numbers of the us personnel and supporting troops as well as the timeframe of the military exercise are still to be discussed and decided by the philippine government and the united states . &quot;
philippine defense secretary reyes told media reporters that the us major general weber will arrive in the philippines soon to &quot; discuss all kinds of conditions and details regarding the operation in sulu . &quot;
sulu , the archipelago in the southern philippines , includes the island of jolo .
golez , arroyo &apos;s national security advisor , said that the military exercise in sulu will &quot; give the philippine armed forces the maximum training in counter-terrorism . &quot;
since the terrorist attacks on the united states in 2001 , the us government has been increasing its military assistance to the philippine government , concerned that the al qaeda islamic militants driven out by the us-led military actions in afghanistan may have established their base in southeast asia .
the above concern has been fully confirmed by the bombing incident in the resort island of bali in indonesia last year , which killed nearly 200 people .
most of those who died in the bali bombing were western tourists .
schmid , founder of german telephone operator mobilcom , declares bankruptcy
( afp , hamburg , february 18 ) schmid , the founder and also the former chairman of german telephone operator mobilcom , has declared himself insolvent today due to the sharp decline in the value of his shares and has filed the application with flensburg court in northern germany .
schmid holds about 40 % of this company that he founded . over the past year , the company has been financially struggling on the brink of bankruptcy , which led to the sharp drop of its share price .
the statement pointed out that schmid &apos;s personal assets and properties are also affected .
the court has appointed accountant gellert to be in charge of his bankruptcy case .
schmid has been spending so much on the next generation umts network development over the time that he was ousted last year by france telecom , the major shareholder of mobilcom .
mobilcom said in a statement later today that schmid &apos;s personal bankruptcy has no effect on the company &apos;s operation or contract .
the statement added that there will be no change on the rescue plan of about 7 billion euros undertaken by france telecom . according to this rescue plan , the german government and financial institutions will provide about 100 million euros of financing to mobilcom , which currently employs about 5,000 people .
us-south korean military exercise to be held in march ; north korea threatens to quit armistice agreement
( afp , seoul , february 18 ) south korea and the united states are going to conduct a large-scale military exercise starting from early march , that will last nearly a month . north korea , in response , threatens to quit the armistice agreement that ended the korean war .
at a time when the tensions caused by the nuclear stand-off on the korean peninsula have continued for four months and showed no sign of easing off , north korea &apos;s threat to quit the armistice agreement can be generally interpreted as pyongyang authorities &apos; response to the announcement made by the united states and south korea yesterday of the joint military exercise to be held in march .
the statement issued by the north korean military accuses the united states of repeatedly violating the armistice agreement : &quot; if the us side continues violating and misusing the armistice agreement as it pleases , there will be no need for north korea to remain bound to the armistice agreement uncomfortably .
the future development will depend entirely on the us attitude . &quot;
however , the us top military officials said that north korea had said they would no longer be bound to the armistice agreement as early as in 1994 .
us authorities announced yesterday that the united states and south korea will hold their annual joint military exercise on the korean peninsula from march 4 to april 2 .
a south korean government official said that south korea issued an invitation to north korea yesterday , asking them to send observers to watch this military exercise .
the official , who did not want to be named , said : &quot; north korea &apos;s statement to quit the armistice agreement is obviously a response to the upcoming joint military exercise by the united states and south korea . &quot;
earlier , the united states ordered 12 b-52 bombers and the same number of b-1 bombers to get ready to go to areas around the korean peninsula . north korea strongly denounced this move .
in addition , the japanese media reported yesterday that the united states has planned to step up its military deployment in northeast asia in order to guard against the concerns triggered by north korea &apos;s nuclear weapons program .
indonesian authorities reject proposal to increase security protection of us embassy
( afp , jakarta , february 19 ) the us embassy in jakarta proposed to indonesian authorities that a 3-meter-high surrounding wall be built to increase the security of the embassy , but the proposal was rejected .
&quot; the jakarta post &quot; and the state-owned &quot; antala &quot; news agency both reported today that jakarta authorities rejected this proposal to build a wall to replace the fence that now separates the embassy and the residences from the outside on grounds that it is aesthetically unacceptable .
jakarta officials , quoting mayor sutiyoso , pointed out that the wall can be built , provided that it be built five meters away from the existing fence inside the embassy compound .
in addition , the embassy must put sod and plant flowers in between the two fences to improve the look of the embassy compound .
sutiyoso indicated that landscaping can reduce the feeling of the us embassy as a citadel .
since around the time the united states led the military actions in afghanistan aimed to overthrow the taliban regime in 2001 , its embassy in indonesia has been endlessly confronted with protesting activities .
that year , when the former ambassador protested against the jakarta police for failing to effectively stop the threat from the hardline islamic groups on the safety of the americans , the relevant authorities increased the security protection of the embassy .
it is generally expected that large-scale protests will become inevitable if the united states launches military actions against iraq .
sony to actively promote playstation 2 to cyber world
( afp , tokyo ) japan &apos;s electronics giant sony corp said that it will start the sales of broadband connection units for the family playstation 2 in retail stores across japan in may to promote the all-popular sony game console further to cyber world .
as of the end of december , seven months after sony promoted its online gaming service in the home market of japan , sony has only sold 190,000 broadband connection units .
the broadband connection unit , which consists of a hard drive and an adapter , is currently available for purchase only through internet service providers .
the aforementioned actual sales figure is disproportional , considering there are 12.5 million playstation 2 users in japan and as many as 50.4 million users worldwide .
starting sales of connection kits in retail stores in tandem with promotion of more online games is part of sony &apos;s strategy to encourage users to use playstation to play online games .
a spokeswoman for sony computer entertainment ( sce ) , a sony subsidiary , said : &quot; we &apos;ll sell connection kits in stores so that more users can enjoy the fun of online games . &quot;
the spokeswoman noted that of the 874 playstation 2 games currently available , only one is authentic online game . two online games will be added in the coming few months .
about 20 games sold in japan have some online capabilities .
the price of the broadband connection kit is not yet decided , but the one sold through isps is priced at 18,000 yen ( 150 us dollars ) per kit .
sony has already sold about 570,000 units of narrowband connection kits in north america at the price of about 39 us dollars and some 20 compatible games .
asia to have largest number of programmers in the world in 2 years
( afp , singapore , february 24 ) a report released by international data corp. today pointed out that in the coming two years , there will be more computer programmers and other professional developers in the asia-pacific region than in north america .
in 2001 , north america had the largest concentration of professional developers , while the asia-pacific region replaced europe to become the area with the second largest number of professional developers .
however , the idc report said that the strong growth in china and india is expected to push the asia-pacific region to the top by 2005 .
asian regions , especially india , are the main source of it professionals in north america .
idc said : &quot; in five years , the growth in the asia-pacific region , especially in those big countries such as china and india , is expected to be much stronger than in north america . &quot;
idc said that there were 7.8 million professional developers in 2001 , and the number is expected to grow to 13.3 million by 2006 .
the report pointed out that by the end of 2001 , there were 1.7 million professional developers in asia .
idc noted that the drop in the number of it professionals in north america is partly due to the decline of technology sector in the region .
study shows father &apos;s genes may affect timing of birth
( afp , paris , february 28 ) according to a report of a danish study to be published on saturday &apos;s &quot; british medical journal , &quot; a father &apos;s genes may affect the timing of a child &apos;s birth .
about 5 % of pregnant women go past their term , with a gestational length of 294 days .
at present , this problem is known to have effects on the health of both mother and child , but what causes it remains a mystery .
the danish researchers tracked 43,000 cases of birth from 1980 to 1992 . the targeted women have at least two children and had a post-term pregnancy for the first delivery .
only the data of their first two deliveries are used for analysis .
overall , of those women who had a prolonged pregnancy for the first delivery , nearly 20 % had the same experience for their second pregnancy .
however , when the first and the second child had different fathers , the rate dropped to just a little bit over 15 % .
olesen , the lead author of the research report , told afp : &quot; this is already a lot .
this means if you ( with the second child ) have the same partner , then compared with those who change their partners , your chance of having a prolonged pregnancy will be over 30 % . &quot;
the research report said : &quot; if a woman changes her partner every time she gets pregnant , it may reduce the risk of reoccurrence of post-term delivery .
we believe this is a new finding .
but the result means the timing of birth may be decided by a father &apos;s genes . &quot;
belgium demands prompt pumping of fuel oil from anchored oil tanker
xinhua news agency , brussels , january 4 ( reporter liu saijun ) belgian authorities issued an ultimatum on the 4th to the owner of the vicky , a turkish ship that anchored in the belgian waters , demanding that he start pumping the 700 to 1,000 tons of fuel oil carried on the tanker at the latest from 8 : 00 a.m. on the 5th .
the belgian media quoted the head of a relevant agency as saying that the fuel oil carried on the vicky is the same as the fuel oil on the prestige , which has polluted the coastal areas off spain , and that the owner of the tanker must ensure prompt pumping of the fuel oil to prevent a vast area of the belgian waters from being polluted .
belgian authorities said that if the owner of the vicky does not meet the above demand , belgium will seize the fuel oil on the ship and contract a professional firm at its own discretion to pump the oil at the owner &apos;s cost .
bound for new york , the vicky started out in antwerp of belgium on the 1st and anchored about 30 kilometers off the ostend coast in northern belgium after it ran into the freighter tricolor that had sunken last month while sailing through the dover strait .
parts of europe battered by floods
xinhua news agency , berlin , january 4 some areas in several european countries such as germany , belgium and the czech republic are recently hit by hurricanes and floods , which killed at least 7 people .
with water levels rising in many rivers , traffic on some of the major waterways are disrupted ; and highway and rail transportation are also affected .
in the state of bavaria in germany , floods overflowed the river banks and inundated the adjacent areas on the 4th , forcing residents to wade through the waist-high water .
the small town of wertheim is expected to experience the highest water level in 80 years .
volunteers ferried local residents in rubber boats to the stores for shopping .
in addition , the government officials have platforms built in the old town areas to make it easier for people to get around .
the famous historic city of cologne also narrowly escaped the disaster in the heavy rains .
the traffic on the 144-kilometer-long rhine south of cologne has to be suspended .
however , government officials said as the river water is continuously receding , the worst time is over .
the floods in the small belgian town of ninove , however , remain serious . two people are already missing .
the belgian government has decided to call on the military to build sandbag embankments to prevent the villages and roads from further ravages .
sri lanka &apos;s prime minister calls on the people to work together for permanent peace
xinhua news agency , colombo , january 6 ( reporter zhang yadong ) on the 5th , sri lanka &apos;s prime minister ranil wickremasinghe called on the people to work together to end the 19-year ethnic conflict in the country and bring about permanent peace .
on the very same night , wickremasinghe said in a national televised address that the negotiations between sri lankan government and the anti-government liberation tigers of tamil eelam ( ltte ) have entered a decisive stage where nothing could keep them away from the negotiation table as it is now the time to start a journey to permanent peace .
he emphasized that it is still a long way to go before peace can be finally materialized while solving the ethnic conflicts through political channels will ensure the interests of all ethnic groups .
he called on all the parties involved to put aside political differences and speak with one voice determined to seek peace .
sri lankan government and ltte will start the four-day fourth round of peace talks on the 6th in nakhon pathom , thailand .
one of the main topics for this talk is the settlement of tamils , who have been displaced in the war , in the high security zones on jaffna peninsula in northern sri lanka . however , the government and ltte have been seriously divided on the issue lately .
sri lankan government forces proposed disarmament of ltte as the condition for resettlement of tamil civilians , but ltte claimed that condition is &quot; unacceptable and unrealistic . &quot;
sri lankan government and ltte signed an agreement in february last year , and both sides started to enforce an official cease-fire .
three rounds of peace talks have been held between both parties since september .
ltte has indicated that it will no longer attempt to establish an independent tamil state through war in the northern and eastern sri lanka and will instead seek autonomous rule of the region under a federal system .
clay sculpture of a goat from fengxiang , shaanxi , becomes mascot of chinese year of the goat
xinhua news agency , xi &apos;an , january 8 the clay sculpture of a goat , the work of hu xinming , a folk artist in liuying village , fengxiang county in shaanxi province , has been voted simultaneously as the mascot of the chinese year of the goat at the time it was selected as the design of the 2003 zodiac stamp .
this is a mascot that chinese have voted for the first time for their own new year .
since the end of september 2002 , more than 50 media agencies nationwide , including china &apos;s central tv station , have jointly held an open solicitation in the country for the mascot of the 2003 year of the goat .
up till the end of december 2002 , the review committee had received over 3,000 entries on the theme of the &quot; goat . &quot;
among &quot; goats &quot; of various features , the clay sculpture of a goat submitted by the folk artist huxinming from shaanxi , with its &quot; charming naivety and auspicious merriment , &quot; won the hearts of most reviewers .
it eventually won the laureate of the mascot of the year of the goat by an absolute majority vote .
baoji area in shaanxi province has long enjoyed the reputation as &quot; the land of folk arts and crafts . &quot; in 1995 and 2002 , piggy pillow , a work of handicraft by a folk artist in longxian county , baoji , and the clay sculpture of a horse by the veteran folk artist hu shen from liuying village , fengxiang county , were respectively selected by the china state post bureau as the designs of zodiac stamps for the years , which were distributed both at home and abroad .
hu xinming &apos;s clay sculpture of a goat marks the third time a work of folk handicraft from baoji area has been selected by the china state post bureau general as the design of a zodiac stamp .
hague tribunal medical team to verify bobetko &apos;s illness in croatia
xinhua news agency , belgrade january 8 ( reporter yang chengming ) from zagreb : the croatian media disclosed on the 8th that the hague tribunal will soon send a medical team to croatia to verify whether bobetko , the former croatian army chief of staff and a war crime suspect wanted by the hague tribunal , is too sick to stand trial .
bobetko was hospitalized for treatment in the middle of last november .
racan , the prime minister of croatia , once promised him that he will not be extradited to the hague tribunal while he is hospitalized .
a spokesperson for the international criminal tribunal for the former yugoslavia issued a statement on september 20 last year , saying that the tribunal had officially demanded that the croatian government arrest and extradite bobetko , who committed &quot; crimes against humanity and war crimes . &quot;
bobetko served as the croatian army chief of staff from november 1992 to july 1995 .
the hague tribunal indicted him for ordering his subordinates in killing over 100 serbian civilians and soldiers and in burning down 300 residential houses in september 1993 .
bobetko issued a statement to the media on the very night , denying the hague tribunal &apos;s indictment and saying he would never yield to the hague tribunal , even if it costs his life .
us defense department calls off 2 missile intercept tests
xinhua news agency , washington , january 8 ( reporter tan xinmu ) lehner , spokesman for the missile defense agency at the pentagon , announced on the 8th that the us military authorities have decided to call off the two missile intercept tests scheduled for the first half of this year because the development of a new type of booster that launches the interceptor is behind the original schedule .
lehner told the media here that the missile defense agency this year will need to concentrate on solving the problem of the booster and that the next missile intercept test will be conducted after boeing manufactures the new type of booster this fall .
boeing originally planned to begin flight tests in 2000 on the new booster that carries the missile &quot; interceptor , &quot; but the tests were postponed due to technical reasons .
after the failure to launch the booster in december 2001 , boeing decided to redesign it and planned to complete the design by this fall .
in the previous eight ground-based missile intercept tests , the us military used a modified &quot; minuteman &quot; rocket as a surrogate booster , but the results of the tests on this kind of booster were not satisfactory .
the missile intercept tests conducted in july 2000 and last december were not successful because the &quot; interceptor &quot; failed to separate from the booster .
us president bush ordered the pentagon to start planning a missile defense system on december 17 last year and try to set up a preliminary missile defense system by september 2004 .
however , many experts think as far as technologies are concerned , the time is not yet ripe to set up a missile defense system .
kadish , director of the missile defense agency , also indicated that if boeing fails to manufacture the desired booster as scheduled , the entire missile defense system set-up will be affected .
slovakian president leaves shanghai for hong kong by air
xinhua news agency , shanghai , january 10 ( reporter zhou jierong ) president rudolf schuster of the slovak republic concluded his visit to shanghai on the morning of the 10th and left shanghai for hong kong on a slovakian charter plane .
zhou muyao , deputy mayor of shanghai , went to see off slovakian president schuster and his entourage at the airport .
schuster and his entourage arrived in shanghai for a visit from beijing on a charter plane at the noon of the 8th .
