the report said that the united states asked turkey for permissions to open a &quot; northern front &quot; in its military strikes against iraq from the turkish territories and to use turkish bases and ports and deploy 80,000 ground troops in turkey so as to launch strikes on baghdad from turkey .
the united states hopes that its military experts can begin inspection and construction on the turkish bases and ports as soon as possible so that the facilities can meet the requirements of the actual warfare .
the three bases that the united states proposed for use are incirlik , batman and diyarbakir ; the three ports are tasucu , mersin and iskenderun .
all of them are located in southern and southeastern turkey .
us resumes admission of iraqi refugees
xinhua news agency , washington , january 10 officials from the un refugee agency said that the us government announced the resumption of its program of admitting iraqi refugees on the 10th after it was briefly suspended .
officials from the us immigration and naturalization service said that the admission of iraqi refugees has now resumed after being suspended for a few days , but they did not explain why the program was suspended or resumed .
on the 9th , the un high commissioner for refugees representative in washington received a phone call from a top us state department official and was told that the admission program of iraqi refugees had been suspended .
the refugees affected by this change are mainly scattered in jordan , syria and turkey .
lavinia limon , the executive director of the us committee for refugees , blamed the plight of these refugees on iraqi president saddam because they had to flee their homeland due to the persecution they suffer at the hands of saddam &apos;s regime .
the us government plans to admit 70,000 refugees in 2003 .
last year , the planned quota for refugees was also 70,000 , but only fewer than 30,000 people were actually admitted .
( entertainment hotline ) peking opera of the fairy tale &quot; the wild swans &quot; to debut on the capital &apos;s stage
xinhua news agency , beijing , january 11 &quot; the wild swans , &quot; a peking opera based on anderson &apos;s fairy tale performed by peking opera house of hebei province , will make its debut on the capital &apos;s stage -- changan theater on evenings from january 13 to january 24 .
