( hk , macau , taiwan ) mainland tourists show strong purchasing power in macau
xinhua news agency , macau , february 14 ( reporter li jie ) in recent years , not only has the number of mainland tourists to macau been increasing but their purchasing power has also been growing rapidly .
according to official statistics released by macau sar government , non-resident tourists spent 4.7 billion patacas in macau in the fourth quarter last year . among them , mainland tourists spent 3.3 billion patacas , topping all the tourists from different places of residence .
since mainland china eased up its policy on overseas travels , the number of mainland tourists taking package tours to hong kong and macau , and going on overseas tours beyond has soared .
of the 11.53 million visitors macau hosted last year , 4.24 million were from mainland china . with the number of visitors coming to macau surpassing that to hong kong for the first time in the fourth quarter last year , mainland china has become the largest source of tourists for macau .
although these tourists stay in macau for an average of 28.8 hours , the average spending per capita reached 2,560 patacas , 64 % higher than the mean value spent by tourists from all places .
analyses show that jewelry and watches , clothing and fabrics , are the hottest commodities among all tourists , accounting respectively for 27 % and 23 % of their spending in macau .
the average non-shopping spending , excluding gambling , was 837 patacas per capita , of which food and beverage , and accommodation , the two major categories , accounted for 41 % and 36 % respectively .
( international ) studies find preemies &apos; learning disabilities surmountable
xinhua news agency , washington , february 15 low birth-weight preemies are generally slow in their mental development and may easily encounter learning disabilities .
researchers at yale university in the united states recently found that this kind of learning disabilities can be surmounted as preemies grow older .
studies confirm that the neurological system of preemies with birth weight lower than 1,500 gram is prone to problems . as many as 50 % of such preemies need special care while attending school .
although many earlier experiments show that animals can recover from initial brain damages , there haven &apos;t been any related reports of preemies &apos; recovery from brain damage .
according to the media report here , researchers at yale university have tracked and monitored 300 children born prematurely and given them iq tests when they were at ages of 3 , 4 1 / 2 , 6 , and 8 . most of them are found to continuously gain their learning abilities as time passes .
tests show that of the preemies classified as &quot; mentally retarded &quot; at the age of 3 , half have reached the average level in verbal comprehension and iq tests after five years .
however , about 23 % of the infants have shown no improvement of their mental development due to their severe brain damage caused by cerebral hemorrhage .
researchers said one of the key factors in the mental development of preemies lies in the family environment .
children who are from a family of three and whose mothers had high levels of education scored better in iq tests .
